29\", \"Q5\", \"Q4964182\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Ferguson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Ferguson\"}, {\"begin\": 515, \"end\": 524, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.306694662769439e-22, \"text\": \"Polynesia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ByHannah Beech Photographs\", \"from\": 415, \"to\": 441}, {\"ngram\": \"a week\", \"from\": 495, \"to\": 501}, {\"ngram\": \"the impact\", \"from\": 535, \"to\": 545}, {\"ngram\": \"nuclear testing\", \"from\": 549, \"to\": 564}, {\"ngram\": \"a territory\", \"from\": 568, \"to\": 579}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic surfing competitions\", \"from\": 596, \"to\": 628}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fifty years ago this July, as the waters of the South Pacific rushed toward the shores of Teahupo'o in a perfect, powerful curl, as they have always done, another wave visited the tiny hamlet.\", \"from\": 634, \"to\": 826, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the waters\", \"from\": 664, \"to\": 674}, {\"ngram\": \"the South Pacific\", \"from\": 678, \"to\": 695}, {\"ngram\": \"the shores\", \"from\": 710, \"to\": 720}, {\"ngram\": \"Teahupo'o\", \"from\": 724, \"to\": 733}, {\"ngram\": \"a perfect, powerful curl\", \"from\": 737, \"to\": 761}, {\"ngram\": \"another wave\", \"from\": 789, \"to\": 801}, {\"ngram\": \"the tiny hamlet\", \"from\": 810, \"to\": 825}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This time it was an invisible and airborne one: a surge of radiation escaping from a nuclear weapon test conducted by France in this far-flung reach of their republic.\", \"from\": 827, \"to\": 994, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 945, \"end\": 951, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999225074164, \"rank\": 7.74920298686891e-08, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a surge\", \"from\": 875, \"to\": 882}, {\"ngram\": \"radiation\", \"from\": 886, \"to\": 895}, {\"ngram\": \"a nuclear weapon test\", \"from\": 910, \"to\": 931}, {\"ngram\": \"this far-flung reach\", \"from\": 955, \"to\": 975}, {\"ngram\": \"their republic\", \"from\": 979, \"to\": 993}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Roniu Tupana Poareu was born in Teahupo'o, her family home fringed by palm trees and hibiscus bushes.\", \"from\": 996, \"to\": 1097, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Roniu Tupana Poareu\", \"from\": 996, \"to\": 1015}, {\"ngram\": \"Teahupo'o\", \"from\": 1028, \"to\": 1037}, {\"ngram\": \"her family home\", \"from\": 1039, \"to\": 1054}, {\"ngram\": \"palm trees\", \"from\": 1066, \"to\": 1076}, {\"ngram\": \"hibiscus bushes\", \"from\": 1081, \"to\": 1096}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She now serves as its mayor and speaks proudly of how its azure wave - a platonic ideal ofcoiled, frothy propulsion- was selected as the site of the surfing competition in these Summer Olympics, being hosted half a world away in Paris.\", \"from\": 1098, \"to\": 1333, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1327, \"end\": 1332, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.994698371681408e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its mayor\", \"from\": 1116, \"to\": 1125}, {\"ngram\": \"its azure wave\", \"from\": 1152, \"to\": 1166}, {\"ngram\": \"a platonic ideal\", \"from\": 1169, \"to\": 1185}, {\"ngram\": \"frothy propulsion-\", \"from\": 1196, \"to\": 1214}, {\"ngram\": \"the site\", \"from\": 1231, \"to\": 1239}, {\"ngram\": \"the surfing competition\", \"from\": 1243, \"to\": 1266}, {\"ngram\": \"these Summer Olympics\", \"from\": 1270, \"to\": 1291}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Teahupo'o concealed a secret behind its sunny tourist brochure seascape.\", \"from\": 1335, \"to\": 1411, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a secret\", \"from\": 1359, \"to\": 1367}, {\"ngram\": \"its sunny tourist brochure seascape\", \"from\": 1375, \"to\": 1410}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unbeknown to its residents, Teahupo'o recorded, according to declassified French military documents, some of the highest radiation readings on Tahiti, French Polynesia's most populated island, after a radioactive cloud unexpectedly drifted overhead in July 1974.\", \"from\": 1412, \"to\": 1674, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1486, \"end\": 1492, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.9999992127326011, \"rank\": 7.760955941025154e-07, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 1555, \"end\": 1561, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.9828930709740282, \"rank\": 0.01740466947164687, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its residents\", \"from\": 1425, \"to\": 1438}, {\"ngram\": \"Teahupo'o\", \"from\": 1440, \"to\": 1449}, {\"ngram\": \"the highest radiation readings\", \"from\": 1521, \"to\": 1551}, {\"ngram\": \"French Polynesia's most populated island\", \"from\": 1563, \"to\": 1603}, {\"ngram\": \"a radioactive cloud\", \"from\": 1611, \"to\": 1630}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 1664, \"to\": 1668}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ms. Poareu's siblings, who, like other children then, were particularly vulnerable to the malignant effects of a nuclear fallout, developed the kinds of cancers associated with exposure to radiation.\", \"from\": 1676, \"to\": 1875, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Ms. Poareu's siblings\", \"from\": 1676, \"to\": 1697}, {\"ngram\": \"other children\", \"from\": 1709, \"to\": 1723}, {\"ngram\": \"the malignant effects\", \"from\": 1762, \"to\": 1783}, {\"ngram\": \"a nuclear fallout\", \"from\": 1787, \"to\": 1804}, {\"ngram\": \"the kinds\", \"from\": 1816, \"to\": 1825}, {\"ngram\": \"cancers\", \"from\": 1829, \"to\": 1836}, {\"ngram\": \"exposure\", \"from\": 1853, \"to\": 1861}, {\"ngram\": \"radiation\", \"from\": 1865, \"to\": 1874}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Other relatives were diagnosed, too, and other villagers died.\", \"from\": 1876, \"to\": 1938, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Other relatives\", \"from\": 1876, \"to\": 1891}, {\"ngram\": \"other villagers\", \"from\": 1917, \"to\": 1932}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A few years ago, Ms. Poareu went house to house in Teahupo'o, a village of 1,500, and discovered 60 residents living with the disease.\", \"from\": 1939, \"to\": 2073, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Ms. Poareu\", \"from\": 1956, \"to\": 1966}, {\"ngram\": \"house\", \"from\": 1972, \"to\": 1977}, {\"ngram\": \"house\", \"from\": 1981, \"to\": 1986}, {\"ngram\": \"Teahupo'o\", \"from\": 1990, \"to\": 1999}, {\"ngram\": \"a village\", \"from\": 2001, \"to\": 2010}, {\"ngram\": \"60 residents\", \"from\": 2036, \"to\": 2048}, {\"ngram\": \"the disease\", \"from\": 2061, \"to\": 2072}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even as mayor, she had not realized the full toll on her community.\", \"from\": 2074, \"to\": 2141, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"mayor\", \"from\": 2082, \"to\": 2087}, {\"ngram\": \"the full toll\", \"from\": 2110, \"to\": 2123}, {\"ngram\": \"her community\", \"from\": 2127, \"to\": 2140}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2010, after years of refusing to recognize the health consequences of three decades of nuclear testing in French Polynesia, the French government began a process - bureaucratic and buried in paperwork - of recognizing and compensating victims of radiation-linked diseases.\", \"from\": 2143, \"to\": 2418, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2259, \"end\": 2268, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.306694662769439e-22, \"text\": \"Polynesia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\"}, {\"begin\": 2274, \"end\": 2280, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.9999992127326011, \"rank\": 7.760955941025154e-07, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"years\", \"from\": 2158, \"to\": 2163}, {\"ngram\": \"the health consequences\", \"from\": 2189, \"to\": 2212}, {\"ngram\": \"three decades\", \"from\": 2216, \"to\": 2229}, {\"ngram\": \"nuclear testing\", \"from\": 2233, \"to\": 2248}, {\"ngram\": \"paperwork\", \"from\": 2337, \"to\": 2346}, {\"ngram\": \"radiation-linked diseases\", \"from\": 2392, \"to\": 2417}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One of Ms. Poareu's sisters, who had been diagnosed with several cancers, was among the successful applicants.\", \"from\": 2419, \"to\": 2529, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Ms. Poareu's sisters\", \"from\": 2426, \"to\": 2446}, {\"ngram\": \"several cancers\", \"from\": 2476, \"to\": 2491}, {\"ngram\": \"the successful applicants\", \"from\": 2503, \"to\": 2528}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But no amount of official recognition, Ms. Poareu said, could cure her.\", \"from\": 2530, \"to\": 2601, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no amount\", \"from\": 2534, \"to\": 2543}, {\"ngram\": \"official recognition\", \"from\": 2547, \"to\": 2567}, {\"ngram\": \"Ms. Poareu\", \"from\": 2569, \"to\": 2579}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am happy that we have the Olympic surfing, and I am proud that everyone in the world will know Teahupo'o,\\\" Ms. Poareu said.\", \"from\": 2603, \"to\": 2729, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympic surfing\", \"from\": 2628, \"to\": 2647}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 2669, \"to\": 2677}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 2681, \"to\": 2690}, {\"ngram\": \"Teahupo'o\", \"from\": 2701, \"to\": 2710}, {\"ngram\": \"Ms. Poareu\", \"from\": 2713, \"to\": 2723}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But sometimes, when I see the suffering of my family, I hate France.\\\"\", \"from\": 2730, \"to\": 2800, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2792, \"end\": 2798, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999225074164, \"rank\": 7.74920298686891e-08, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the suffering\", \"from\": 2757, \"to\": 2770}, {\"ngram\": \"my family\", \"from\": 2774, \"to\": 2783}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The twin realities of Teahupo'o, both surfing paradise and cancer hot spot, reveal the complicated legacy of colonialism in French Polynesia, a collection of islands and atolls covering an area roughly the size of Western Europe.\", \"from\": 2802, \"to\": 3031, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2933, \"end\": 2942, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.306694662769439e-22, \"text\": \"Polynesia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The twin realities\", \"from\": 2802, \"to\": 2820}, {\"ngram\": \"Teahupo'o\", \"from\": 2824, \"to\": 2833}, {\"ngram\": \"paradise and cancer hot spot\", \"from\": 2848, \"to\": 2876}, {\"ngram\": \"the complicated legacy\", \"from\": 2885, \"to\": 2907}, {\"ngram\": \"colonialism\", \"from\": 2911, \"to\": 2922}, {\"ngram\": \"a collection\", \"from\": 2944, \"to\": 2956}, {\"ngram\": \"islands\", \"from\": 2960, \"to\": 2967}, {\"ngram\": \"atolls\", \"from\": 2972, \"to\": 2978}, {\"ngram\": \"an area\", \"from\": 2988, \"to\": 2995}, {\"ngram\": \"roughly the size\", \"from\": 2996, \"to\": 3012}, {\"ngram\": \"Western Europe\", \"from\": 3016, \"to\": 3030}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As the site of nearly 200 French nuclear tests from 1966 to 1996, French Polynesia developed fast.\", \"from\": 3032, \"to\": 3130, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3058, \"end\": 3078, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_and_weapons_of_mass_destruction\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French nuclear tests\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_and_weapons_of_mass_destruction\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_and_weapons_of_mass_destruction\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the site\", \"from\": 3035, \"to\": 3043}, {\"ngram\": \"French Polynesia\", \"from\": 3098, \"to\": 3114}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Before it started detonating nuclear weapons, Paris gifted Tahiti its first airport and modern port.\", \"from\": 3131, \"to\": 3231, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3177, \"end\": 3182, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.994698371681408e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3190, \"end\": 3196, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.9828930709740282, \"rank\": 0.01740466947164687, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"nuclear weapons\", \"from\": 3160, \"to\": 3175}, {\"ngram\": \"its first airport\", \"from\": 3197, \"to\": 3214}, {\"ngram\": \"modern port\", \"from\": 3219, \"to\": 3230}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Polynesians employed by the nuclear industry left their palm-frond homes to live in newly built housing blocks on Tahiti, the largest of the territory's 120 or so islands.\", \"from\": 3233, \"to\": 3404, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3233, \"end\": 3244, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.9999999999436113, \"rank\": 5.609704005772901e-11, \"text\": \"Polynesians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\"}, {\"begin\": 3347, \"end\": 3353, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.9828930709740282, \"rank\": 0.01740466947164687, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the nuclear industry\", \"from\": 3257, \"to\": 3277}, {\"ngram\": \"their palm-frond homes\", \"from\": 3283, \"to\": 3305}, {\"ngram\": \"newly built housing blocks\", \"from\": 3317, \"to\": 3343}, {\"ngram\": \"the territory's 120 or so islands\", \"from\": 3370, \"to\": 3403}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tourists arrived, too, lured by the coral-edged beaches and tales of a mighty wave at Teahupo'o.\", \"from\": 3405, \"to\": 3501, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Tourists\", \"from\": 3405, \"to\": 3413}, {\"ngram\": \"the coral-edged beaches\", \"from\": 3437, \"to\": 3460}, {\"ngram\": \"tales\", \"from\": 3465, \"to\": 3470}, {\"ngram\": \"a mighty wave\", \"from\": 3474, \"to\": 3487}, {\"ngram\": \"Teahupo'o\", \"from\": 3491, \"to\": 3500}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some families decorated their new apartments with a glowing symbol of Polynesian progress: a framed photograph of a mushroom cloud rising high over a South Pacific atoll.\", \"from\": 3503, \"to\": 3673, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3573, \"end\": 3583, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.9999999999608917, \"rank\": 3.935470235171057e-11, \"text\