.org/resource/Charles_de_Gaulle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_de_Gaulle\"}, {\"begin\": 6730, \"end\": 6746, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French president\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 6780, \"end\": 6789, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.306694662769439e-22, \"text\": \"Polynesia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the war general\", \"from\": 6707, \"to\": 6722}, {\"ngram\": \"their part\", \"from\": 6759, \"to\": 6769}, {\"ngram\": \"the laboratory\", \"from\": 6793, \"to\": 6807}, {\"ngram\": \"the 20th century's most consequential inventions\", \"from\": 6819, \"to\": 6867}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jeanne Puputauki, now 80 and white-haired, remembers the detonation in July 1966 of the very first \\\"champignon,\\\" or \\\"mushroom,\\\" as she put it.\", \"from\": 6870, \"to\": 7012, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6870, \"end\": 6876, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joan_of_Arc\", \"score\": 0.9999999950086931, \"rank\": 4.991410888782745e-09, \"text\": \"Jeanne\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joan_of_Arc\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joan_of_Arc\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the detonation\", \"from\": 6923, \"to\": 6937}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 6941, \"to\": 6945}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"mushroom\", \"from\": 6986, \"to\": 6995}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Excitement thrummed on the volcanic island, with its coral limestone cathedral.\", \"from\": 7013, \"to\": 7092, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Excitement\", \"from\": 7013, \"to\": 7023}, {\"ngram\": \"the volcanic island\", \"from\": 7036, \"to\": 7055}, {\"ngram\": \"its coral limestone cathedral\", \"from\": 7062, \"to\": 7091}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French soldiers and officials descended.\", \"from\": 7093, \"to\": 7133, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7093, \"end\": 7099, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.9999992127326011, \"rank\": 7.760955941025154e-07, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"officials\", \"from\": 7113, \"to\": 7122}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The local population was not given access to a structure adequate enough to protect them from radiation.\", \"from\": 7135, \"to\": 7239, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The local population\", \"from\": 7135, \"to\": 7155}, {\"ngram\": \"access\", \"from\": 7170, \"to\": 7176}, {\"ngram\": \"a structure\", \"from\": 7180, \"to\": 7191}, {\"ngram\": \"radiation\", \"from\": 7229, \"to\": 7238}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The winds shifted suddenly, and danger - odorless, soundless and unseen - advanced toward Mangareva.\", \"from\": 7240, \"to\": 7340, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7330, \"end\": 7339, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mangareva\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2294016618854016e-40, \"text\": \"Mangareva\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mangareva\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mangareva\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The winds\", \"from\": 7240, \"to\": 7249}, {\"ngram\": \"soundless\", \"from\": 7291, \"to\": 7300}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some of the first to die were the island's horses, including three belonging to Ms. Puputauki's family, she said.\", \"from\": 7341, \"to\": 7454, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the island's horses\", \"from\": 7371, \"to\": 7390}, {\"ngram\": \"Ms. Puputauki's family\", \"from\": 7421, \"to\": 7443}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As the nuclear detonations continued, Mangareva residents said that they were only occasionally directed into bunkers.\", \"from\": 7456, \"to\": 7574, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7494, \"end\": 7503, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mangareva\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2294016618854016e-40, \"text\": \"Mangareva\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mangareva\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mangareva\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the nuclear detonations\", \"from\": 7459, \"to\": 7482}, {\"ngram\": \"bunkers\", \"from\": 7566, \"to\": 7573}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They drank rainwater and ate vegetables grown in island soil.\", \"from\": 7575, \"to\": 7636, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"rainwater\", \"from\": 7586, \"to\": 7595}, {\"ngram\": \"vegetables\", \"from\": 7604, \"to\": 7614}, {\"ngram\": \"island soil\", \"from\": 7624, \"to\": 7635}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When the local food seemed to make them sick and lagoon fish went belly up, they resorted to canned alternatives, Ms. Puputauki said.\", \"from\": 7637, \"to\": 7770, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the local food\", \"from\": 7642, \"to\": 7656}, {\"ngram\": \"canned alternatives\", \"from\": 7730, \"to\": 7749}, {\"ngram\": \"Ms. Puputauki\", \"from\": 7751, \"to\": 7764}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French military personnel stationed nearby enjoyed shipments of fresh food procured from outside Mangareva.\", \"from\": 7771, \"to\": 7882, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7775, \"end\": 7781, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.9999992127326011, \"rank\": 7.760955941025154e-07, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 7872, \"end\": 7881, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mangareva\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2294016618854016e-40, \"text\": \"Mangareva\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mangareva\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mangareva\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"nearby enjoyed shipments\", \"from\": 7811, \"to\": 7835}, {\"ngram\": \"fresh food\", \"from\": 7839, \"to\": 7849}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They also could shelter in buildings with thick walls.\", \"from\": 7883, \"to\": 7937, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"buildings\", \"from\": 7910, \"to\": 7919}, {\"ngram\": \"thick walls\", \"from\": 7925, \"to\": 7936}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Throughout, the French government, which first tested its nuclear devices in colonial Algeria, maintained that the detonations were safe, even as evidence from American testing began to indicate otherwise.\", \"from\": 7939, \"to\": 8144, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7955, \"end\": 7961, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.9999992127326011, \"rank\": 7.760955941025154e-07, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 8025, \"end\": 8032, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"score\": 0.9999999499759736, \"rank\": 5.0024264527914446e-08, \"text\": \"Algeria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\"}, {\"begin\": 8099, \"end\": 8107, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999999672582, \"rank\": 3.2486565381838336e-11, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its nuclear devices\", \"from\": 7993, \"to\": 8012}, {\"ngram\": \"the detonations\", \"from\": 8050, \"to\": 8065}, {\"ngram\": \"evidence\", \"from\": 8085, \"to\": 8093}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Military documents that were declassified in 2013 showed alarming radiation levels on Polynesian islands.\", \"from\": 8145, \"to\": 8250, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8231, \"end\": 8241, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.9999999999608917, \"rank\": 3.935470235171057e-11, \"text\": \"Polynesian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Military documents\", \"from\": 8145, \"to\": 8163}, {\"ngram\": \"alarming radiation levels\", \"from\": 8202, \"to\": 8227}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In Mangareva, the rainwater radiation more than two months after the July 1966 detonation was 11 million times higher than normal, one secret report showed.\", \"from\": 8251, \"to\": 8407, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8254, \"end\": 8263, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mangareva\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2294016618854016e-40, \"text\": \"Mangareva\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mangareva\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mangareva\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the rainwater radiation\", \"from\": 8265, \"to\": 8288}, {\"ngram\": \"the July 1966 detonation\", \"from\": 8316, \"to\": 8340}, {\"ngram\": \"one secret report\", \"from\": 8382, \"to\": 8399}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French soldiers who had been stationed at a military base on Hao atoll grew sick.\", \"from\": 8408, \"to\": 8489, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8408, \"end\": 8414, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.9999992127326011, \"rank\": 7.760955941025154e-07, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 8469, \"end\": 8478, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hao_(French_Polynesia)\", \"score\": 0.9999999610226958, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hao atoll\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hao_(French_Polynesia)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hao_(French_Polynesia)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a military base\", \"from\": 8450, \"to\": 8465}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thyroid disease, which Mangareva residents said had never afflicted the island before the tests, became common.\", \"from\": 8491, \"to\": 8602, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8514, \"end\": 8523, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mangareva\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2294016618854016e-40, \"text\": \"Mangareva\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mangareva\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mangareva\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Thyroid disease\", \"from\": 8491, \"to\": 8506}, {\"ngram\": \"the island\", \"from\": 8559, \"to\": 8569}, {\"ngram\": \"the tests\", \"from\": 8577, \"to\": 8586}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tears trickling down her cheeks, Ms. Puputauki listed family members who had died of the types of cancers that have been linked to radiation: her mother, her father, two sisters, her brother-in-law.\", \"from\": 8603, \"to\": 8801, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her cheeks\", \"from\": 8624, \"to\": 8634}, {\"ngram\": \"Ms. Puputauki\", \"from\": 8636, \"to\": 8649}, {\"ngram\": \"family members\", \"from\": 8657, \"to\": 8671}, {\"ngram\": \"the types\", \"from\": 8688, \"to\": 8697}, {\"ngram\": \"cancers\", \"from\": 8701, \"to\": 8708}, {\"ngram\": \"radiation\", \"from\": 8734, \"to\": 8743}, {\"ngram\": \"her mother\", \"from\": 8745, \"to\": 8755}, {\"ngram\": \"her father\", \"from\": 8757, \"to\": 8767}, {\"ngram\": \"two sisters\", \"from\": 8769, \"to\": 8780}, {\"ngram\": \"her brother\", \"from\": 8782, \"to\": 8793}, {\"ngram\": \"law\", \"from\": 8797, \"to\": 8800}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her grandson died of a brain tumor at age 6.\", \"from\": 8802, \"to\": 8846, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Her grandson\", \"from\": 8802, \"to\": 8814}, {\"ngram\": \"a brain tumor\", \"from\": 8823, \"to\": 8836}, {\"ngram\": \"age\", \"from\": 8840, \"to\": 8843}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Now it's my turn,\\\" Ms. Puputauki said.\", \"from\": 8848, \"to\": 8887, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my turn\", \"from\": 8858, \"to\": 8865}, {\"ngram\": \"Ms. Puputauki\", \"from\": 8868, \"to\": 8881}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She clutched a string of shells and a crucifix in her hand.\", \"from\": 8888, \"to\": 8947, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a string\", \"from\": 8901, \"to\": 8909}, {\"ngram\": \"shells\", \"from\": 8913, \"to\": 8919}, {\"ngram\": \"a crucifix\", \"from\": 8924, \"to\": 8934}, {\"ngram\": \"her hand\", \"from\": 8938, \"to\": 8946}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A wreath of flowers and ferns sat on her head.\", \"from\": 8948, \"to\": 8994, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A wreath\", \"from\": 8948, \"to\": 8956}, {\"ngram\": \"flowers\", \"from\": 8960, \"to\": 8967}, {\"ngram\": \"ferns\", \"from\": 8972, \"to\": 8977}, {\"ngram\": \"her head\", \"from\": 8985, \"to\": 8993}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She has been diagnosed with two separate cancers.\", \"from\": 8996, \"to\": 9045, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"two separate cancers\", \"from\": 9024, \"to\": 9044}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I love my island and it's my home, so I will stay,\\\" Ms. Puputauki said.\", \"from\": 9047, \"to\": 9119, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my island\", \"from\": 9055, \"to\": 9064}, {\"ngram\": \"my home\", \"from\": 9074, \"to\": 9081}, {\"ngram\": \"Ms. Puputauki\", \"from\": 9100, \"to\": 9113}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But it's destroyed.\\\"\", \"from\": 9120, \"to\": 9141, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The healing process was supposed to begin in 2010, when the French Parliament passed a law allowing affected military personnel and civilians to apply for compensation from diseases precipitated by the nuclear fallout.\", \"from\": 9143, \"to\": 9361, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9203, \"end\": 9220, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Parliament\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.052884875585301e-74, \"text\": \"French Parliament\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q11204\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Parliament\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Parliament\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The healing process\", \"from\": 9143, \"to\": 9162}, {\"ngram\": \"a law\", \"from\": 9228, \"to\": 9233}, {\"ngram\": \"affected military personnel\", \"from\": 9243, \"to\": 9270}, {\"ngram\": \"civilians\", \"from\": 9275, \"to\": 9284}, {\"ngram\": \"compensation\", \"from\": 9298, \"to\": 9310}, {\"ngram\": \"diseases\", \"from\": 9316, \"to\": 9324}, {\"ngram\": \"the nuclear fallout\", \"from\": 9341, \"to\": 9360}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the specifics, including an initial requirement that applicants prove that their sicknesses had been caused by exposure to radiation, heightened frustrations.\", \"from\": 9362, \"to\": 9524, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"But the specifics\", \"from\": 9362, \"to\": 9379}, {\"ngram\": \"an initial requirement\", \"from\": 9391, \"to\": 9413}, {\"ngram\": \"applicants\", \"from\": 9419, \"to\": 9429}, {\"ngram\": \"their sicknesses\", \"from\": 9441, \"to\": 9457}, {\"ngram\": \"exposure\", \"from\": 9477, \"to\": 9485}, {\"ngram\": \"radiation\", \"from\": 9489, \"to\": 9498}, {\"ngram\": \"heightened frustrations\", \"from\": 9500, \"to\": 9523}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the first seven years, only 11 victims had their applications approved.\", \"from\": 9526, \"to\": 9600, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first seven years\", \"from\": 9529, \"to\": 9550}, {\"ngram\": \"only 11 victims\", \"from\": 9552, \"to\": 9567}, {\"ngram\": \"their applications\", \"from\": 9572, \"to\": 9590}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After various tweaks to the process, 108 people were given official status in 2023, but that is still just a fraction of those thought to have been affected.\", \"from\": 9601, \"to\": 9758, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"various tweaks\", \"from\": 9607, \"to\": 9621}, {\"ngram\": \"the process\", \"from\": 9625, \"to\": 9636}, {\"ngram\": \"108 people\", \"from\": 9638, \"to\": 9648}, {\"ngram\": \"official status\", \"from\": 9660, \"to\": 9675}, {\"ngram\": \"just a fraction\", \"from\": 9703, \"to\": 9718}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Polynesian officials have suggested that about 10,000 people were exposed to high blasts of radiation, but outside researchers say that roughly 110,000 were directly affected, nearly 90 percent of the population in the 1970s.\", \"from\": 9759, \"to\": 9984, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9759, \"end\": 9769, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.9999999999608917, \"rank\": 3.935470235171057e-11, \"text\": \"Polynesian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"about 10,000 people\", \"from\": 9800, \"to\": 9819}, {\"ngram\": \"high blasts\", \"from\": 9836, \"to\": 9847}, {\"ngram\": \"radiation\", \"from\": 9851, \"to\": 9860}, {\"ngram\": \"outside researchers\", \"from\": 9866, \"to\": 9885}, {\"ngram\": \"the population\", \"from\": 9956, \"to\": 9970}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1970s\", \"from\": 9974, \"to\": 9983}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Perhaps to signal that the military has nothing to hide, in March, a group of Polynesian politicians was escorted to Mururoa, which is normally off-limits.\", \"from\": 9986, \"to\": 10141, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10064, \"end\": 10074, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.9999999999608917, \"rank\": 3.935470235171057e-11, \"text\": \"Polynesian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\"}, {\"begin\": 10103, \"end\": 10110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moruroa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mururoa\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moruroa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moruroa\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the military\", \"from\": 10009, \"to\": 10021}, {\"ngram\": \"nothing\", \"from\": 10026, \"to\": 10033}, {\"ngram\": \"March\", \"from\": 10046, \"to\": 10051}, {\"ngram\": \"a group\", \"from\": 10053, \"to\": 10060}, {\"ngram\": \"off-limits\", \"from\": 10130, \"to\": 10140}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A military doctor showed radiation readings from the atoll, which were normal.\", \"from\": 10142, \"to\": 10220, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A military doctor\", \"from\": 10142, \"to\": 10159}, {\"ngram\": \"radiation readings\", \"from\": 10167, \"to\": 10185}, {\"ngram\": \"the atoll\", \"from\": 10191, \"to\": 10200}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Other officers explained how the nuclear waste - estimated at hundreds of kilograms of plutonium - was safely disposed of in deep wells.\", \"from\": 10221, \"to\": 10357, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Other officers\", \"from\": 10221, \"to\": 10235}, {\"ngram\": \"the nuclear waste\", \"from\": 10250, \"to\": 10267}, {\"ngram\": \"hundreds\", \"from\": 10283, \"to\": 10291}, {\"ngram\": \"kilograms\", \"from\": 10295, \"to\": 10304}, {\"ngram\": \"plutonium\", \"from\": 10308, \"to\": 10317}, {\"ngram\": \"deep wells\", \"from\": 10346, \"to\": 10356}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The legislators, however, had many questions.\", \"from\": 10359, \"to\": 10404, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The legislators\", \"from\": 10359, \"to\": 10374}, {\"ngram\": \"many questions\", \"from\": 10389, \"to\": 10403}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They asked why certain marine life wasn't tested for radiation.\", \"from\": 10405, \"to\": 10468, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"certain marine life\", \"from\": 10420, \"to\": 10439}, {\"ngram\": \"radiation\", \"from\": 10458, \"to\": 10467}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They wondered whether switching from atmospheric tests to underground explosions, which while safer in many ways, had put the nuclear site at threat of partial collapse.\", \"from\": 10469, \"to\": 10638, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"atmospheric tests\", \"from\": 10506, \"to\": 10523}, {\"ngram\": \"underground explosions\", \"from\": 10527, \"to\": 10549}, {\"ngram\": \"many ways\", \"from\": 10572, \"to\": 10581}, {\"ngram\": \"the nuclear site\", \"from\": 10591, \"to\": 10607}, {\"ngram\": \"threat\", \"from\": 10611, \"to\": 10617}, {\"ngram\": \"partial collapse\", \"from\": 10621, \"to\": 10637}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The French government told us for many years that everything was safe, but it wasn't,\\\" said Mereana Reid Arbelot, who is the French Polynesian representative at the French National Assembly and a member of the delegation that toured Mururoa.\", \"from\": 10640, \"to\": 10882, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10645, \"end\": 10651, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.9999992127326011, \"rank\": 7.760955941025154e-07, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 10766, \"end\": 10772, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.9999992127326011, \"rank\": 7.760955941025154e-07, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 10806, \"end\": 10830, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Parliament\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5044738561133874e-70, \"text\": \"French National Assembly\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q11204\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Parliament\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Parliament\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 10668, \"to\": 10670}, {\"ngram\": \"many years\", \"from\": 10675, \"to\": 10685}, {\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 10691, \"to\": 10701}, {\"ngram\": \"Mereana Reid Arbelot\", \"from\": 10733, \"to\": 10753}, {\"ngram\": \"a member\", \"from\": 10835, \"to\": 10843}, {\"ngram\": \"the delegation\", \"from\": 10847, \"to\": 10861}, {\"ngram\": \"Mururoa\", \"from\": 10874, \"to\": 10881}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's hard to have trust.\\\"\", \"from\": 10883, \"to\": 10909, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"trust\", \"from\": 10902, \"to\": 10907}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Memories linger of how France hid its dirty nuclear past.\", \"from\": 10911, \"to\": 10968, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10934, \"end\": 10940, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999225074164, \"rank\": 7.74920298686891e-08, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Memories\", \"from\": 10911, \"to\": 10919}, {\"ngram\": \"its dirty nuclear past\", \"from\": 10945, \"to\": 10967}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And they reach far beyond French Polynesia.\", \"from\": 10969, \"to\": 11012, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11002, \"end\": 11011, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.306694662769439e-22, \"text\": \"Polynesia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In 1985, the Rainbow Warrior, a boat owned by the environmental group Greenpeace, was in the Pacific to protest nuclear testing when it exploded in a harbor of Auckland, New Zealand, killing one person aboard.\", \"from\": 11013, \"to\": 11222, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11083, \"end\": 11093, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greenpeace\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.91848987530032e-44, \"text\": \"Greenpeace\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greenpeace\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greenpeace\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Rainbow Warrior\", \"from\": 11022, \"to\": 11041}, {\"ngram\": \"a boat\", \"from\": 11043, \"to\": 11049}, {\"ngram\": \"the Pacific\", \"from\": 11102, \"to\": 11113}, {\"ngram\": \"nuclear testing\", \"from\": 11125, \"to\": 11140}, {\"ngram\": \"a harbor\", \"from\": 11161, \"to\": 11169}, {\"ngram\": \"Auckland\", \"from\": 11173, \"to\": 11181}, {\"ngram\": \"New Zealand\", \"from\": 11183, \"to\": 11194}, {\"ngram\": \"one person\", \"from\": 11204, \"to\": 11214}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It had been headed next for Mururoa, and the French government eventually admitted that its intelligence service had bombed the boat.\", \"from\": 11223, \"to\": 11356, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11268, \"end\": 11274, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.9999992127326011, \"rank\": 7.760955941025154e-07, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Mururoa\", \"from\": 11251, \"to\": 11258}, {\"ngram\": \"its intelligence service\", \"from\": 11311, \"to\": 11335}, {\"ngram\": \"the boat\", \"from\": 11347, \"to\": 11355}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Last century, a groundswell of independence freed scores of nations from colonialism.\", \"from\": 11358, \"to\": 11443, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a groundswell\", \"from\": 11372, \"to\": 11385}, {\"ngram\": \"independence\", \"from\": 11389, \"to\": 11401}, {\"ngram\": \"scores\", \"from\": 11408, \"to\": 11414}, {\"ngram\": \"nations\", \"from\": 11418, \"to\": 11425}, {\"ngram\": \"colonialism\", \"from\": 11431, \"to\": 11442}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Today, fewer than 20 places, almost all small islands controlled by the United States, United Kingdom and France, remain tethered to a larger power.\", \"from\": 11444, \"to\": 11592, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11516, \"end\": 11529, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9927272388793658, \"rank\": 0.007326041672042971, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 11531, \"end\": 11545, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9976151540276578, \"rank\": 0.0023905470554515117, \"text\": \"United Kingdom\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 11550, \"end\": 11556, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999225074164, \"rank\": 7.74920298686891e-08, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"fewer than 20 places\", \"from\": 11451, \"to\": 11471}, {\"ngram\": \"almost all small islands\", \"from\": 11473, \"to\": 11497}, {\"ngram\": \"a larger power\", \"from\": 11577, \"to\": 11591}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When the United Nations drew up a list of non-self-governing territories in 1946 - in an attempt to highlight the dangers of the imperialism that had fueled World War II - French Polynesia was part of the tally.\", \"from\": 11594, \"to\": 11805, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11603, \"end\": 11617, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7028703617664842e-23, \"text\": \"United Nations\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a list\", \"from\": 11626, \"to\": 11632}, {\"ngram\": \"non-self-governing territories\", \"from\": 11636, \"to\": 11666}, {\"ngram\": \"an attempt\", \"from\": 11680, \"to\": 11690}, {\"ngram\": \"the dangers\", \"from\": 11704, \"to\": 11715}, {\"ngram\": \"the imperialism\", \"from\": 11719, \"to\": 11734}, {\"ngram\": \"World War II - French Polynesia\", \"from\": 11751, \"to\": 11782}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 11787, \"to\": 11791}, {\"ngram\": \"the tally\", \"from\": 11795, \"to\": 11804}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But France soon requested its removal, and the territory did not return to the list until 2013, after lobbying by the pro-independence Tavini party.\", \"from\": 11806, \"to\": 11954, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11810, \"end\": 11816, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999225074164, \"rank\": 7.74920298686891e-08, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its removal\", \"from\": 11832, \"to\": 11843}, {\"ngram\": \"the territory\", \"from\": 11849, \"to\": 11862}, {\"ngram\": \"the list\", \"from\": 11881, \"to\": 11889}, {\"ngram\": \"the pro-independence Tavini party\", \"from\": 11920, \"to\": 11953}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As recently as last year, a French official said at the U.N. that French Polynesia had no place on the decolonization list.\", \"from\": 11955, \"to\": 12078, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11983, \"end\": 11989, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.9999992127326011, \"rank\": 7.760955941025154e-07, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 12011, \"end\": 12015, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.5312533287309814e-23, \"text\": \"U.N.\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations\"}, {\"begin\": 12028, \"end\": 12037, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.306694662769439e-22, \"text\": \"Polynesia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"last year\", \"from\": 11970, \"to\": 11979}, {\"ngram\": \"no place\", \"from\": 12042, \"to\": 12050}, {\"ngram\": \"the decolonization list\", \"from\": 12054, \"to\": 12077}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The debate over independence continues.\", \"from\": 12080, \"to\": 12119, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The debate\", \"from\": 12080, \"to\": 12090}, {\"ngram\": \"independence\", \"from\": 12096, \"to\": 12108}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mr. Brotherson, the president of French Polynesia, refers to his land as a \\\"country,\\\" and it has been referred to in French officialdom by the unwieldy designation of \\\"overseas country inside the Republic.\\\"\", \"from\": 12120, \"to\": 12326, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12160, \"end\": 12169, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.306694662769439e-22, \"text\": \"Polynesia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\"}, {\"begin\": 12237, \"end\": 12243, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.9999992127326011, \"rank\": 7.760955941025154e-07, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Mr. Brotherson\", \"from\": 12120, \"to\": 12134}, {\"ngram\": \"the president\", \"from\": 12136, \"to\": 12149}, {\"ngram\": \"his land\", \"from\": 12181, \"to\": 12189}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"country\", \"from\": 12193, \"to\": 12203}, {\"ngram\": \"the unwieldy designation\", \"from\": 12259, \"to\": 12283}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"overseas country\", \"from\": 12287, \"to\": 12304}, {\"ngram\": \"the Republic\", \"from\": 12312, \"to\": 12324}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yet Mr. Brotherson also acknowledges the convenience of having a French passport.\", \"from\": 12327, \"to\": 12408, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12392, \"end\": 12407, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_nationality_law\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0777647121627272e-39, \"text\": \"French passport\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_nationality_law\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_nationality_law\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Mr. Brotherson\", \"from\": 12331, \"to\": 12345}, {\"ngram\": \"the convenience\", \"from\": 12364, \"to\": 12379}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unless the ind\\u00e9pendantistes, as they are known, can offer judicial, health and education services that approach those of France, he knows that any independence referendum will fail.\", \"from\": 12409, \"to\": 12590, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12530, \"end\": 12536, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999225074164, \"rank\": 7.74920298686891e-08, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the ind\\u00e9pendantistes\", \"from\": 12416, \"to\": 12436}, {\"ngram\": \"judicial, health and education services\", \"from\": 12467, \"to\": 12506}, {\"ngram\": \"any independence referendum\", \"from\": 12552, \"to\": 12579}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Perhaps, Mr. Brotherson said, a sovereign French Polynesia could one day negotiate a deal in which Paris would be responsible for the islands' defense and security but not for other aspects of nationhood.\", \"from\": 12592, \"to\": 12796, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12641, \"end\": 12650, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.306694662769439e-22, \"text\": \"Polynesia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\"}, {\"begin\": 12691, \"end\": 12696, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.994698371681408e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Mr. Brotherson\", \"from\": 12601, \"to\": 12615}, {\"ngram\": \"a deal\", \"from\": 12675, \"to\": 12681}, {\"ngram\": \"the islands' defense\", \"from\": 12722, \"to\": 12742}, {\"ngram\": \"security\", \"from\": 12747, \"to\": 12755}, {\"ngram\": \"other aspects\", \"from\": 12768, \"to\": 12781}, {\"ngram\": \"nationhood\", \"from\": 12785, \"to\": 12795}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Or perhaps the United States, which maintains such pacts with several Pacific countries, could be a possible partner, he said.\", \"from\": 12797, \"to\": 12923, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12812, \"end\": 12825, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9927272388793658, \"rank\": 0.007326041672042971, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"such pacts\", \"from\": 12843, \"to\": 12853}, {\"ngram\": \"several Pacific countries\", \"from\": 12859, \"to\": 12884}, {\"ngram\": \"a possible partner\", \"from\": 12895, \"to\": 12913}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If colonialism is an anachronism, Mr. Brotherson continued in fluent English, use of the French language might be even more so.\", \"from\": 12924, \"to\": 13051, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13013, \"end\": 13028, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.999978593666964, \"rank\": 2.1406791222840106e-05, \"text\": \"French language\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"colonialism\", \"from\": 12927, \"to\": 12938}, {\"ngram\": \"an anachronism\", \"from\": 12942, \"to\": 12956}, {\"ngram\": \"Mr. Brotherson\", \"from\": 12958, \"to\": 12972}, {\"ngram\": \"fluent English\", \"from\": 12986, \"to\": 13000}, {\"ngram\": \"use\", \"from\": 13002, \"to\": 13005}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yet because of its territorial holdings in the world's oceans, France can project its power across the globe.\", \"from\": 13052, \"to\": 13161, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13115, \"end\": 13121, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999225074164, \"rank\": 7.74920298686891e-08, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its territorial holdings\", \"from\": 13067, \"to\": 13091}, {\"ngram\": \"the world's oceans\", \"from\": 13095, \"to\": 13113}, {\"ngram\": \"its power\", \"from\": 13134, \"to\": 13143}, {\"ngram\": \"the globe\", \"from\": 13151, \"to\": 13160}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French Polynesia was once self-sufficient, populated by masterful sailors who navigated their canoes between distant islands.\", \"from\": 13163, \"to\": 13288, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13170, \"end\": 13179, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.306694662769439e-22, \"text\": \"Polynesia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"masterful sailors\", \"from\": 13219, \"to\": 13236}, {\"ngram\": \"their canoes\", \"from\": 13251, \"to\": 13263}, {\"ngram\": \"distant islands\", \"from\": 13272, \"to\": 13287}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Today, the territory imports 70 percent of its food.\", \"from\": 13289, \"to\": 13341, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the territory\", \"from\": 13296, \"to\": 13309}, {\"ngram\": \"70 percent\", \"from\": 13318, \"to\": 13328}, {\"ngram\": \"its food\", \"from\": 13332, \"to\": 13340}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Seventy percent of the population lives on a single island, Tahiti, as a consequence of rapid urbanization after the nuclear construction boom.\", \"from\": 13342, \"to\": 13485, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13402, \"end\": 13408, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.9828930709740282, \"rank\": 0.01740466947164687, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Seventy percent\", \"from\": 13342, \"to\": 13357}, {\"ngram\": \"the population\", \"from\": 13361, \"to\": 13375}, {\"ngram\": \"a single island\", \"from\": 13385, \"to\": 13400}, {\"ngram\": \"a consequence\", \"from\": 13413, \"to\": 13426}, {\"ngram\": \"rapid urbanization\", \"from\": 13430, \"to\": 13448}, {\"ngram\": \"the nuclear construction boom\", \"from\": 13455, \"to\": 13484}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many Polynesians, even laborers at the testing sites who have suffered a particularly high incidence of disease, prefer not to talk about the nuclear legacy, said Tamatoa Tepuhiarii, who works for a local group that has helped Polynesian nuclear workers and their families.\", \"from\": 13487, \"to\": 13760, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13492, \"end\": 13503, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.9999999999436113, \"rank\": 5.609704005772901e-11, \"text\": \"Polynesians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\"}, {\"begin\": 13714, \"end\": 13724, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.9999999999608917, \"rank\": 3.935470235171057e-11, \"text\": \"Polynesian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"even laborers\", \"from\": 13505, \"to\": 13518}, {\"ngram\": \"the testing sites\", \"from\": 13522, \"to\": 13539}, {\"ngram\": \"a particularly high incidence\", \"from\": 13558, \"to\": 13587}, {\"ngram\": \"disease\", \"from\": 13591, \"to\": 13598}, {\"ngram\": \"the nuclear legacy\", \"from\": 13625, \"to\": 13643}, {\"ngram\": \"Tamatoa Tepuhiarii\", \"from\": 13650, \"to\": 13668}, {\"ngram\": \"a local group\", \"from\": 13684, \"to\": 13697}, {\"ngram\": \"their families\", \"from\": 13745, \"to\": 13759}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The workers exulted in how their salaries allowed them to buy exotic imports.\", \"from\": 13761, \"to\": 13838, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The workers\", \"from\": 13761, \"to\": 13772}, {\"ngram\": \"their salaries\", \"from\": 13788, \"to\": 13802}, {\"ngram\": \"exotic imports\", \"from\": 13823, \"to\": 13837}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They used to say that with all the money they earned, they could eat so much butter,\\\" Mr. Tepuhiarii said.\", \"from\": 13840, \"to\": 13947, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all the money\", \"from\": 13868, \"to\": 13881}, {\"ngram\": \"so much butter\", \"from\": 13910, \"to\": 13924}, {\"ngram\": \"Mr. Tepuhiarii\", \"from\": 13927, \"to\": 13941}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But, you know, how much butter can you really eat?\\\"\", \"from\": 13948, \"to\": 14000, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"how much butter\", \"from\": 13964, \"to\": 13979}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many French Polynesians, particularly on the outer islands, know little about the dangers of the tests.\", \"from\": 14002, \"to\": 14105, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14007, \"end\": 14013, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.9999992127326011, \"rank\": 7.760955941025154e-07, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 14014, \"end\": 14025, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.9999999999436113, \"rank\": 5.609704005772901e-11, \"text\": \"Polynesians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the outer islands\", \"from\": 14043, \"to\": 14060}, {\"ngram\": \"the dangers\", \"from\": 14080, \"to\": 14091}, {\"ngram\": \"the tests\", \"from\": 14095, \"to\": 14104}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The territory is, per capita, one of the largest suppliers of young people to the French military, the same force that built and ran the nuclear test sites at Mururoa and Fangataufa.\", \"from\": 14106, \"to\": 14288, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14188, \"end\": 14194, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.9999992127326011, \"rank\": 7.760955941025154e-07, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 14277, \"end\": 14287, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fangataufa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fangataufa\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fangataufa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fangataufa\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The territory\", \"from\": 14106, \"to\": 14119}, {\"ngram\": \"capita\", \"from\": 14128, \"to\": 14134}, {\"ngram\": \"the largest suppliers\", \"from\": 14143, \"to\": 14164}, {\"ngram\": \"young people\", \"from\": 14168, \"to\": 14180}, {\"ngram\": \"the same force\", \"from\": 14205, \"to\": 14219}, {\"ngram\": \"the nuclear test sites\", \"from\": 14239, \"to\": 14261}, {\"ngram\": \"Mururoa\", \"from\": 14265, \"to\": 14272}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We need to talk about getting compensation for the victims of the nuclear tests,\\\" Mr. Tepuhiarii said.\", \"from\": 14290, \"to\": 14393, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"compensation\", \"from\": 14321, \"to\": 14333}, {\"ngram\": \"the victims\", \"from\": 14338, \"to\": 14349}, {\"ngram\": \"the nuclear tests\", \"from\": 14353, \"to\": 14370}, {\"ngram\": \"Mr. Tepuhiarii\", \"from\": 14373, \"to\": 14387}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But the most important thing is to decolonize the minds of Indigenous peoples.\\\"\", \"from\": 14394, \"to\": 14474, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the most important thing\", \"from\": 14399, \"to\": 14423}, {\"ngram\": \"the minds\", \"from\": 14441, \"to\": 14450}, {\"ngram\": \"Indigenous peoples\", \"from\": 14454, \"to\": 14472}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French researchers had calculated carefully, predicting the interplay of wind, weather and radiation.\", \"from\": 14476, \"to\": 14581, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14480, \"end\": 14486, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.9999992127326011, \"rank\": 7.760955941025154e-07, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the interplay\", \"from\": 14536, \"to\": 14549}, {\"ngram\": \"wind\", \"from\": 14553, \"to\": 14557}, {\"ngram\": \"weather\", \"from\": 14559, \"to\": 14566}, {\"ngram\": \"radiation\", \"from\": 14571, \"to\": 14580}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But on July 17, 1974, the mushroom cloud from France's final atmospheric nuclear test - before the switch to underground detonations - did not rise as high as scientists had anticipated.\", \"from\": 14582, \"to\": 14768, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14628, \"end\": 14634, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999225074164, \"rank\": 7.74920298686891e-08, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 14589, \"to\": 14593}, {\"ngram\": \"the mushroom cloud\", \"from\": 14604, \"to\": 14622}, {\"ngram\": \"the switch\", \"from\": 14677, \"to\": 14687}, {\"ngram\": \"underground detonations\", \"from\": 14691, \"to\": 14714}, {\"ngram\": \"scientists\", \"from\": 14741, \"to\": 14751}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Without the winds of a higher altitude, the cloud of radiation barreled directly toward Tahiti, some 740 miles away from Mururoa.\", \"from\": 14769, \"to\": 14898, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14857, \"end\": 14863, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.9828930709740282, \"rank\": 0.01740466947164687, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\"}, {\"begin\": 14890, \"end\": 14897, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moruroa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mururoa\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moruroa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moruroa\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the winds\", \"from\": 14777, \"to\": 14786}, {\"ngram\": \"a higher altitude\", \"from\": 14790, \"to\": 14807}, {\"ngram\": \"radiation\", \"from\": 14822, \"to\": 14831}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What happened next was laid bare in the declassified French military documents.\", \"from\": 14900, \"to\": 14979, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14953, \"end\": 14959, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.9999992127326011, \"rank\": 7.760955941025154e-07, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Scientists soon realized where the prevailing winds were forcing the radioactive cloud.\", \"from\": 14980, \"to\": 15067, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Scientists\", \"from\": 14980, \"to\": 14990}, {\"ngram\": \"the prevailing winds\", \"from\": 15011, \"to\": 15031}, {\"ngram\": \"the radioactive cloud\", \"from\": 15045, \"to\": 15066}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It would take nearly two days for the fallout to reach Tahiti, yet residents were not made fully aware of the risks.\", \"from\": 15068, \"to\": 15184, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15123, \"end\": 15129, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.9828930709740282, \"rank\": 0.01740466947164687, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"nearly two days\", \"from\": 15082, \"to\": 15097}, {\"ngram\": \"the fallout\", \"from\": 15102, \"to\": 15113}, {\"ngram\": \"residents\", \"from\": 15135, \"to\": 15144}, {\"ngram\": \"the risks\", \"from\": 15174, \"to\": 15183}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When a French commission decided who in Tahiti could apply for compensation over fallout, eligibility was mostly limited to residents who lived on one part of the island, based in part on radiation readings taken across Tahiti that were published in 2006 in a French atomic energy commission report.\", \"from\": 15186, \"to\": 15485, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15193, \"end\": 15199, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.9999992127326011, \"rank\": 7.760955941025154e-07, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 15226, \"end\": 15232, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.9828930709740282, \"rank\": 0.01740466947164687, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\"}, {\"begin\": 15406, \"end\": 15412, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.9828930709740282, \"rank\": 0.01740466947164687, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\"}, {\"begin\": 15446, \"end\": 15477, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Alternative_Energies_and_Atomic_Energy_Commission\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French atomic energy commission\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Alternative_Energies_and_Atomic_Energy_Commission\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Alternative_Energies_and_Atomic_Energy_Commission\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"compensation\", \"from\": 15249, \"to\": 15261}, {\"ngram\": \"fallout\", \"from\": 15267, \"to\": 15274}, {\"ngram\": \"eligibility\", \"from\": 15276, \"to\": 15287}, {\"ngram\": \"residents\", \"from\": 15310, \"to\": 15319}, {\"ngram\": \"one part\", \"from\": 15333, \"to\": 15341}, {\"ngram\": \"the island\", \"from\": 15345, \"to\": 15355}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 15366, \"to\": 15370}, {\"ngram\": \"radiation readings\", \"from\": 15374, \"to\": 15392}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But ananalysis of the declassified paperwork and other radiological databy an investigative consortium including S\\u00e9bastien Philippe, a research scholar at Princeton University's Program on Science and Global Security, showed that the report had significantly minimized the radiation exposure across the island.\", \"from\": 15486, \"to\": 15796, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15599, \"end\": 15617, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/S\\u00e9bastien_Philippe\", \"score\": 0.9999994468582083, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"S\\u00e9bastien Philippe\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q378622\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/S\\u00e9bastien_Philippe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/S\\u00e9bastien_Philippe\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ananalysis\", \"from\": 15490, \"to\": 15500}, {\"ngram\": \"the declassified paperwork\", \"from\": 15504, \"to\": 15530}, {\"ngram\": \"an investigative consortium\", \"from\": 15561, \"to\": 15588}, {\"ngram\": \"a research scholar\", \"from\": 15619, \"to\": 15637}, {\"ngram\": \"Princeton University's Program\", \"from\": 15641, \"to\": 15671}, {\"ngram\": \"Science\", \"from\": 15675, \"to\": 15682}, {\"ngram\": \"Global Security\", \"from\": 15687, \"to\": 15702}, {\"ngram\": \"the report\", \"from\": 15716, \"to\": 15726}, {\"ngram\": \"the radiation exposure\", \"from\": 15755, \"to\": 15777}, {\"ngram\": \"the island\", \"from\": 15785, \"to\": 15795}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Defenders of the 2006 report initially said that the International Atomic Energy Agency had validated its findings.\", \"from\": 15798, \"to\": 15913, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15851, \"end\": 15885, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Atomic_Energy_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Atomic Energy Agency\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Atomic_Energy_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Atomic_Energy_Agency\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Defenders\", \"from\": 15798, \"to\": 15807}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2006 report\", \"from\": 15811, \"to\": 15826}, {\"ngram\": \"its findings\", \"from\": 15900, \"to\": 15912}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Polynesian legislators and activists discovered that the international body had validated only the report's methodology, not the data.\", \"from\": 15914, \"to\": 16052, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15918, \"end\": 15928, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.9999999999608917, \"rank\": 3.935470235171057e-11, \"text\": \"Polynesian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"activists\", \"from\": 15945, \"to\": 15954}, {\"ngram\": \"the international body\", \"from\": 15971, \"to\": 15993}, {\"ngram\": \"only the report's methodology\", \"from\": 16008, \"to\": 16037}, {\"ngram\": \"the data\", \"from\": 16043, \"to\": 16051}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am not a political person, and for a long time I did not want to speak out because people assumed that if you talk about the nuclear issue then you must be pro-independence,\\\" said L\\u00e9na Normand, vice president of Association 193, which helps Polynesians navigate the compensation bureaucracy.\", \"from\": 16054, \"to\": 16348, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 16298, \"end\": 16309, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.9999999999436113, \"rank\": 5.609704005772901e-11, \"text\": \"Polynesians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a political person\", \"from\": 16064, \"to\": 16082}, {\"ngram\": \"a long time\", \"from\": 16092, \"to\": 16103}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 16140, \"to\": 16146}, {\"ngram\": \"the nuclear issue\", \"from\": 16178, \"to\": 16195}, {\"ngram\": \"L\\u00e9na Normand\", \"from\": 16237, \"to\": 16249}, {\"ngram\": \"vice president\", \"from\": 16251, \"to\": 16265}, {\"ngram\": \"Association\", \"from\": 16269, \"to\": 16280}, {\"ngram\": \"the compensation bureaucracy\", \"from\": 16319, \"to\": 16347}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But people need to know what happened and how things are still being covered up.\\\"\", \"from\": 16349, \"to\": 16431, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 16354, \"to\": 16360}, {\"ngram\": \"things\", \"from\": 16396, \"to\": 16402}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Melody Lihault was raised in Tahiti.\", \"from\": 16433, \"to\": 16469, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 16462, \"end\": 16468, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.9828930709740282, \"rank\": 0.01740466947164687, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Melody Lihault\", \"from\": 16433, \"to\": 16447}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her father often flew to the archipelago that includes Mururoa and Fangataufa for his pearl-farming business.\", \"from\": 16470, \"to\": 16579, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 16537, \"end\": 16547, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fangataufa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fangataufa\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fangataufa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fangataufa\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Her father\", \"from\": 16470, \"to\": 16480}, {\"ngram\": \"the archipelago\", \"from\": 16495, \"to\": 16510}, {\"ngram\": \"Mururoa\", \"from\": 16525, \"to\": 16532}, {\"ngram\": \"his pearl-farming business\", \"from\": 16552, \"to\": 16578}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2002, when she was 14 years old, she was diagnosed with lymphoma and sent to suburban Paris for treatment because there were no adequate facilities back home.\", \"from\": 16580, \"to\": 16741, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 16669, \"end\": 16674, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.994698371681408e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"lymphoma\", \"from\": 16639, \"to\": 16647}, {\"ngram\": \"treatment\", \"from\": 16679, \"to\": 16688}, {\"ngram\": \"no adequate facilities\", \"from\": 16708, \"to\": 16730}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ms. Lihault's parents had the money to come with her, but the other Polynesian children in the pediatric cancer ward - and there were quite a few, particularly from the islands closer to the testing sites, she said - were hospitalized alone.\", \"from\": 16742, \"to\": 16983, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Ms. Lihault's parents\", \"from\": 16742, \"to\": 16763}, {\"ngram\": \"the money\", \"from\": 16768, \"to\": 16777}, {\"ngram\": \"the pediatric cancer ward\", \"from\": 16833, \"to\": 16858}, {\"ngram\": \"the islands\", \"from\": 16907, \"to\": 16918}, {\"ngram\": \"the testing sites\", \"from\": 16929, \"to\": 16946}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ms. Lihault's parents tried to comfort them, bringing in tropical flowers and organizing a ukulele party in the dark, cold Parisian winter.\", \"from\": 16984, \"to\": 17123, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Ms. Lihault's parents\", \"from\": 16984, \"to\": 17005}, {\"ngram\": \"tropical flowers\", \"from\": 17041, \"to\": 17057}, {\"ngram\": \"a ukulele party\", \"from\": 17073, \"to\": 17088}, {\"ngram\": \"the dark, cold Parisian winter\", \"from\": 17092, \"to\": 17122}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2016, she was diagnosed again with lymphoma, a separate cancer from her first one, her doctors told her.\", \"from\": 17125, \"to\": 17232, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"lymphoma\", \"from\": 17163, \"to\": 17171}, {\"ngram\": \"a separate cancer\", \"from\": 17173, \"to\": 17190}, {\"ngram\": \"her doctors\", \"from\": 17211, \"to\": 17222}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She has been officially recognized as a victim of the nuclear fallout and is now in remission.\", \"from\": 17233, \"to\": 17327, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a victim\", \"from\": 17271, \"to\": 17279}, {\"ngram\": \"the nuclear fallout\", \"from\": 17283, \"to\": 17302}, {\"ngram\": \"remission\", \"from\": 17317, \"to\": 17326}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The declassified documents hold further surprises.\", \"from\": 17329, \"to\": 17379, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The declassified documents\", \"from\": 17329, \"to\": 17355}, {\"ngram\": \"further surprises\", \"from\": 17361, \"to\": 17378}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One map shows that the highest radiation reading recorded on the entire island of Tahiti was in Teahupo'o, the village that is hosting the Olympic surfing event.\", \"from\": 17380, \"to\": 17541, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 17462, \"end\": 17468, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.9828930709740282, \"rank\": 0.01740466947164687, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"One map\", \"from\": 17380, \"to\": 17387}, {\"ngram\": \"the highest radiation reading\", \"from\": 17399, \"to\": 17428}, {\"ngram\": \"the entire island\", \"from\": 17441, \"to\": 17458}, {\"ngram\": \"Teahupo'o\", \"from\": 17476, \"to\": 17485}, {\"ngram\": \"the village\", \"from\": 17487, \"to\": 17498}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic surfing event\", \"from\": 17515, \"to\": 17540}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yet when a version of that map was published in the 2006 report, the reading from Teahupo'o was omitted.\", \"from\": 17542, \"to\": 17646, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a version\", \"from\": 17551, \"to\": 17560}, {\"ngram\": \"that map\", \"from\": 17564, \"to\": 17572}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2006 report\", \"from\": 17590, \"to\": 17605}, {\"ngram\": \"the reading\", \"from\": 17607, \"to\": 17618}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One day in March, a group of young surfers sat under a shade tree on the beach at Teahupo'o.\", \"from\": 17648, \"to\": 17740, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"March\", \"from\": 17659, \"to\": 17664}, {\"ngram\": \"a group\", \"from\": 17666, \"to\": 17673}, {\"ngram\": \"young surfers\", \"from\": 17677, \"to\": 17690}, {\"ngram\": \"a shade tree\", \"from\": 17701, \"to\": 17713}, {\"ngram\": \"the beach\", \"from\": 17717, \"to\": 17726}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Powerful waves rolled in.\", \"from\": 17741, \"to\": 17766, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Powerful waves\", \"from\": 17741, \"to\": 17755}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The villagers had heard complaints about how construction for the Olympics had damaged the coral reef and destroyed wetlands needed to absorb the rains that regularly lash the area.\", \"from\": 17767, \"to\": 17948, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The villagers\", \"from\": 17767, \"to\": 17780}, {\"ngram\": \"complaints\", \"from\": 17791, \"to\": 17801}, {\"ngram\": \"construction\", \"from\": 17812, \"to\": 17824}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 17829, \"to\": 17841}, {\"ngram\": \"the coral reef\", \"from\": 17854, \"to\": 17868}, {\"ngram\": \"wetlands\", \"from\": 17883, \"to\": 17891}, {\"ngram\": \"the rains\", \"from\": 17909, \"to\": 17918}, {\"ngram\": \"the area\", \"from\": 17939, \"to\": 17947}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Teahupo'o's nuclear legacy was something they had never really considered.\", \"from\": 17949, \"to\": 18027, \"entities\": [], \"nou